=== Pronunciation ===
[[Category:Hebrew language]]
עלם  -  עולם / ‛ôlâm  ‛ôlâm / o-lawm', o-lawm'
=== Etymology ===

From {{HH|5956}}; 
=== Adjective ===
properly concealed, that is, the vanishing point; generally time out of mind (past or future), that is, (practically) eternity; frequentative adverbially (especially with prepositional prefix) always: - always (-s), ancient (time), any more, continuance, eternal, (for, [n-]) ever (-lasting, -more, of old), lasting, long (time), (of) old (time), perpetual, at any time, (beginning of the) world (+ without end). Compare H5331, H5703.